Content:
This is another reason why it was a good idea to have my big application consist of only one public file which can easily be whitelisted. Everything else lives outside the web root and is never directly executed.<p><pre><code>    location ~ ^/index\.php {
        proxy_pass   http://localhost:8080;
    }
</code></pre>
Everything else in the web root is static files and can be served directly. The rest of the application uses an URL routing scheme based on PATH_INFO
